Dynamic libraries

SDL - http://www.libsdl.org/
Minimum version: 2.0.3
License: zlib

SDL mixer - http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_mixer/
Minimum version: 2.0.0
License: zlib

zlib - http://www.zlib.net/
Minimum version: 1.2.8
License: zlib

OpenGL - http://www.opengl.org/
Minimum version: 1.0


Static libraries

Extended module player library lite - http://xmp.sourceforge.net/
Minimum version: 4.3.3
License: MIT (Expat)

Basics - https://github.com/atroel/basics/
Minimum version: 0.3
License: 2-clause BSD

Download and build the static libraries beforehand.  Adapt Build.mk accordingly.


Build on Linux

Open Greedy can be built under GNU/Linux using GCC and GNU Make.  Make sure
development packages are installed for the dynamic libraries and run make.


Build on Windows

Open Greedy can be built under Windows using MinGW and GNU Make.  Download SDL2
and SDL2 mixer development archives for Windows and unpack them at the same
level as Open Greedy source tree (or adapt Build-Win32.mk accordingly).  Make
sure development packages are installed for other dynamic libraries and run
make.


Build on Mac OS X

Open Greedy can be built on Mac OS X using GCC and GNU Make.  Download and
install SDL2 and SDL2 mixer for Mac OS X in ~/Library/Frameworks (or in
/Library/Frameworks if you prefer a system-wide installation) and run make.
